rComments: Was lucky enough to be part of Neil's first punk music & culture seminar and would HIGHLY recommend this course to anyone looking for a fun and interesting elective! I knew nothing about punk but Neil made it so accessible. Definitely give this class a go - it allows you to be creative and really engage in interesting class discussions.

Took Punk Culture with him. Class was a seminar and mostly felt like we were chilling have a chat. Super accessible and enjoyable, and yet I've learned alot. Prof. Soiseth is a great teacher; I wish all my seminars were like this one

I took AHL3100 - Rock Music and Society with Professor Soiseth and absolutely loved it. He is an incredibly engaging lecturer and each unit is jam-packed and extremely detailed. His course revolves around three short book reviews (max 5 pages) and a final take-home exam. Yes, you have to read three books - but it's totally worth it.

Where to even begin. In all my years at the University of Ottawa, I have never encountered a worse prof. VERY dry lectures and ridiculous course content. NO specifications are given regarding what is actually relevant on the midterms. The most harsh grading I have ever received. When questioned about it, he was extremely rude and dismissive.

Engaging lecturer, always tries to make the class content interesting. Make sure to take good notes because he does not post slides on Brightspace and he will often give hints as to what content is important for testing. Fair marker but ensure you follow his formatting exactly and footnote properly for the final paper; he will dock marks.

Awesome lecturer. Doesn't use powerpoints and doesn't post notes on Brightspace so be ready to take notes. If you go to class and take notes, you'll be able to get a good grade on the midterms. Both were 20 questions with one-word answers (people, places, events). Final exam was a take-home where you had to write two papers. Term paper was simple.

Soiseth was great. His lectures were entertaining and packed with stuff. His ability to make US history funny and engaging made me always want to go to class. His two midterms are really easy if you've gone to class. The essay was also simple. He let us pick our own topics. Would highly recommend one of his classes.
